Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that has its soma located in some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).
Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that has its soma located in some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).
Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that has its soma located in some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).
Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that has its soma located in some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).

Nerve that exits the ventral nerve cord at the dorsal midline and bifurcates to form two lateral branches to the periphery (Gorczyca et al., 1994; Santos et al., 2006). These nerves are only found in abdominal segments (Gorczyca et al., 1994; Santos et al., 2006).

definition.value: Santos et al. (2006) refer to the proximal region as the median nerve (MeN) and the post-branch point region as the transverse nerve.

value.value: Larval nerve found in segments T1-A7 that has two roots, carrying fibers from the neuromere of the nerve and the immediately anterior neuromere (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It exits the lateral ventral nerve cord in line with the anterior commissure and its proximal region shares a glial sheath with the segmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It extends further dorsally than the segmental nerve, innervating dorsal and lateral groups of muscles and sense organs (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Larval sensory neuron that fasciculates with an intersegmental nerve. In abdominal segments 1-7, these are the sensory neurons located in the dorsal and lateral clusters (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; Singhania and Grueber, 2014).

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ. These neurons are found in the thoracic and abdominal segments, they are relatively ventral within the des cluster, anterior to desB (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ. These neurons are found in the thoracic and abdominal segments, they are relatively ventral within the des cluster, posterior to desA (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ. These neurons are found in the thoracic and abdominal segments, dorsal to desB and ventral to desD (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ. These neurons are found in the thoracic and abdominal segments, they are relatively dorsal within the des cluster, dorsal to desC (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ. These neurons are found only in the thoracic segments, and are the dorsalmost des neurons (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).
A neuron innervating the dorsal Kolbchen of the embryonic/larval prothorax (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). There are two such neurons innervating each dorsal Kolbchen.
Sensory neuron that innervates a dorsal triscolopidial chordotonal organ, located in the dorsal region of a larval thoracic segment.
Sensory neuron that innervates a lateral chordotonal organ of larval abdominal segment 8 or 9.

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a lateral external sense (les) organ. These neurons are found in the thoracic and abdominal segments and they are the ventralmost les neurons (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a lateral external sense (les) organ. These neurons are found in the thoracic and abdominal segments, they are the dorsal to the lesA neurons and ventral to lesC (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a lateral external sense (les) organ. These neurons are found in the thoracic and abdominal segments and they are relatively ventral within the les cluster (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).

Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that innervates a lateral external sense (les) organ. It is found only in the prothoracic segment, ventral to lesC and dorsal to lesB (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).
A neuron innervating the lateral Kolbchen of the embryonic/larval meso- or metathoracic segment (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). There are three such neurons innervating each dorsal Kolbchen.

Larval neuron that innervates the prothoracic lateral triscolopidial chordotonal organ (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Unlike other prothoracic lateral cluster neurons, its axon fasciculates with the mesothoracic segmental nerve, rather than the prothoracic intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). There are three of these cells on each side (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Neuron of abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5. Five of these exist per abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ, numbered 1 to 5 in an anterior to posterior direction (Merritt and Whitington, 1994). Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve.
Larval multidendritic neuron of the dorsal sensory cluster. It is a proprioceptor neuron (Heckscher et al., 2015).

Larval class III multidendritic neuron whose cell body is relatively ventroposterior compared to other multidendritic neurons in the dorsal sensory cluster (Grueber et al., 2002; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005).

definition.value: Following the classification system proposed by Grueber et al. (2002), ddaA is a class III neuron.

value.value: Larval class II multidendritic neuron whose cell body is relatively ventral compared to other multidendritic neurons in the dorsal sensory cluster, slightly dorsal to ddaA (Grueber et al., 2002; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005).

Larval class IV multidendritic neuron whose cell body is located fairly centrally among the dendritic arborizing neurons of the dorsal sensory cluster (Grueber et al., 2002; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005). Its dendrites cover a dorsal region of the body wall of its segment and do not overlap with the dendrites of the anterior ventral (vdaa) neuron (Grueber et al., 2002). Its axon terminals are found in a dorsal region of the nociceptive neuropil (Li et al., 2019).

definition.value: Following the classification system proposed by Grueber et al. (2002), ddaC is a class IV neuron.

value.value: Larval class I multidendritic neuron whose cell body is relatively anterodorsal compared to other multidendritic neurons in the dorsal sensory cluster (Grueber et al., 2002; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005).

definition.value: Referred to as ddaF in Sweeney et al. (2002) - FBrf0148943 and other papers (Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005). The nomenclature used here is according to Grueber et al. (2002).

value.value: Larval class I multidendritic neuron whose cell body is relatively posterodorsal compared to other multidendritic neurons in the dorsal sensory cluster (Grueber et al., 2002; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005).
Any multidendritic neuron (FBbt:00005209) that has its soma located in some larval lateral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007297).

label.value: larval thoracic lateral multidendritic neuron ldaA

value.value: Most ventral multidendritic neuron of the larval thoracic lateral cluster.

definition.value: A-D designation not clear from Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein (1997), but likely to be ventral to dorsal based on Orgogozo and Grueber (2005) - FBrf0183734 and Merritt and Whitington (1995) - FBrf0080250.

label.value: larval thoracic lateral multidendritic neuron ldaB

value.value: Second most ventral multidendritic neuron of the larval thoracic lateral cluster.

definition.value: A-D designation not clear from Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein (1997), but likely to be ventral to dorsal based on Orgogozo and Grueber (2005) - FBrf0183734 and Merritt and Whitington (1995) - FBrf0080250.

label.value: larval thoracic lateral multidendritic neuron ldaC

value.value: Second most dorsal multidendritic neuron of the larval thoracic lateral cluster.

definition.value: A-D designation not clear from Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein (1997), but likely to be ventral to dorsal based on Orgogozo and Grueber (2005) - FBrf0183734 and Merritt and Whitington (1995) - FBrf0080250.

label.value: larval thoracic lateral multidendritic neuron ldaD

value.value: Most dorsal multidendritic neuron of the larval thoracic lateral cluster (Williams and Shepherd, 2002).

Larval nerve found in segments T1-A7 that has two roots, both carrying fibers from the neuromere of the nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It exits the lateral ventral nerve cord in line with the anterior commissure and its proximal region shares a glial sheath with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It does not extend as far dorsally as the intersegmental nerve, and mainly innervates ventral muscles and sense organs (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Larval sensory neuron that fasciculates with a segmental nerve. In abdominal segments 1-7, these are the sensory neurons located in the ventral and ventral' clusters (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; Singhania and Grueber, 2014).
Sensory neuron that innervates a ventral chordotonal organ of the larval abdomen or thorax.
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 of the ventral sensory cluster.
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the posterior hair of a Keilin organ, together with a vesE neuron (Ghysen et al., 1986).
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the posterior hair of a Keilin organ, together with a vesD neuron (Ghysen et al., 1986).

Sensory neuron that innervates the unpaired ventral papilla vas, which is found in abdominal segment 8. Unlike other sensory neurons of abdominal segment 8, it joins the nerve of abdominal segment 9 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Larval sensory neuron found in the ventral' cluster of abdominal segments 1-7 (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986; Bodmer et al., 1989). It develops from a common precursor with the abdominal v'dap (v'pda) neuron (Brewster and Bodmer, 1995; Veling et al., 2019). There are two of these cells per A1-7 hemisegment, and they innervate the vc5 sensillum (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005). It fasciculates in branch a of the segmental nerve, SNa (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Larval sensory neuron that innervates a ventral Kolbchen (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). There is one ventral Kolbchen in each thoracic hemisegment, innervated by three of these cells, found in the ventral' sensory cluster (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986; Bodmer et al., 1989).
Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval prothoracic segment (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986) that innervates a papillar sensilla. It lies on the anterior border, ventral to v''esB.
Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval prothoracic segment (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986) that innervates a papillar sensilla. It lies on the anterior border, dorsal to v''esA.

label.value: larval ventral cluster group multidendritic neuron

value.value: Any multidendritic neuron (FBbt:00005209) that has its soma located in some larval ventral sensory cluster group (FBbt:00007295).

Larval class II multidendritic neuron with its soma in a relatively anterior position in the ventral vdaA-D cluster (Grueber et al., 2003; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005; Veling et al., 2019). Its axon fasciculates with the segmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Larval class IV multidendritic neuron with its soma in the ventral vdaA-D cluster, usually posterior to vdaA and anterior to vdaC and vdaD (Grueber et al., 2003; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005; Veling et al., 2019). Its dendrites cover a ventral region of the body wall of its segment and do not overlap with the dendrites of the anterior ventral (vdaa) neuron (Grueber et al., 2002). Its axon fasciculates with the segmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Its axon terminals are found in a ventral region of the nociceptive neuropil (Li et al., 2019).

Larval class II multidendritic neuron with its soma in a relatively posterior and dorsal position in the ventral vdaA-D cluster (Grueber et al., 2003; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005; Veling et al., 2019). Its axon fasciculates with the segmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Larval class III multidendritic neuron with its soma in a relatively posterior and ventral position in the ventral vdaA-D cluster (Grueber et al., 2003; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005; Veling et al., 2019). Its axon fasciculates with the segmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).
